# Summary: Key Functions Cheat Sheet

| R Function | What it does |
|---|---|
| `scan("url", skip=n)` | Load data from a file/URL, skip n header lines |
| `ts(data, frequency=, start=)` | Convert data to a time series object |
| `plot.ts(x)` | Plot a time series |
| `par(mfrow=c(r,c))` | Arrange multiple plots in r rows and c columns |
| `x11()` | Open a new graphics window |
| `decompose(x)` | Split a time series into Trend + Seasonal + Random |
| `decompose(x, type="multiplicative")` | Same but using multiplicative model |
| `diff(x)` | Compute differences between consecutive values |
| `births.ts.comp$seasonal` | Extract the seasonal component |
| `births.ts.comp$trend` | Extract the trend component |
| `births.ts.comp$random` | Extract the noise/residual component |

